<subSubSection id="C31665519532FF82798CFF6EFE92FF37" box="[151,272,186,212]" pageId="3" pageNumber="56" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BB336DA9532FF82798CFF6EFE92FF37" blockId="3.[151,734,151,212]" box="[151,272,186,212]" pageId="3" pageNumber="56">
(
<figureCitation id="13372A5F9532FF827984FF6EFF6BFF37" box="[159,233,186,212]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,255,1934,1958]" captionTargetBox="[193,1378,357,1874]" captionTargetId="figure-118@2.[151,1436,323,1927]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Trichotoca edentula sp. n., male. A: Fourth flagellomere, lateral view (holotype). B: Apical flagellomeres, lateral view (holotype). C: Maxillary palpus, lateral view (paratype from Mt Weld). D: Wing (paratype from Mt Weld). Scale = 0.05 mm for A–C, 1.0 mm for D." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5241999" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5241999/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="56">Figs 1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13372A5F9532FF8279E3FF6EFE85FF37" box="[248,263,186,212]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,255,1098,1122]" captionTargetBox="[184,1374,188,1048]" captionTargetId="figure-338@4.[151,1436,140,1100]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Trichotoca edentula sp. n., holotype male. A: Terminalia, ventral view. B: Ejaculatory apodeme and tegmen, ventral view. Scale = 0.1 mm for A, 0.05 mm for B." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5242003" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5242003/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="56">2</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C31665519532FF82798CFEDEFDCCFD3F" pageId="3" pageNumber="56" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BB336DA9532FF82798CFEDEFDCCFD3F" blockId="3.[151,1436,266,1132]" pageId="3" pageNumber="56">
<emphasis id="B978EAC89532FF82798CFEDEFE95FEC7" bold="true" box="[151,279,266,292]" pageId="3" pageNumber="56">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C0C4D599532FF827B44FEDEFCCBFEC0" authorityName="Jaschhof &amp; Jaschhof" authorityYear="2008" baseAuthorityName="Jaschhof &amp; Jaschhof" baseAuthorityYear="2008" box="[607,841,266,291]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Trichotoca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fraterna">
<emphasis id="B978EAC89532FF827B44FEDEFCCBFEC0" box="[607,841,266,291]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="56">Trichotoca fraterna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see below) as follows. The necks of the mesal antennal flagellomeres are longer than the nodes (
<figureCitation id="13372A5F9532FF827BC5FEE6FCB8FEAF" box="[734,826,306,332]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,255,1934,1958]" captionTargetBox="[193,1378,357,1874]" captionTargetId="figure-118@2.[151,1436,323,1927]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Trichotoca edentula sp. n., male. A: Fourth flagellomere, lateral view (holotype). B: Apical flagellomeres, lateral view (holotype). C: Maxillary palpus, lateral view (paratype from Mt Weld). D: Wing (paratype from Mt Weld). Scale = 0.05 mm for A–C, 1.0 mm for D." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5241999" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5241999/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="56">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
), but not quite as long as in 
<taxonomicName id="4C0C4D599532FF827D9FFEE6FB66FEA8" authorityName="Jaschhof &amp; Jaschhof" authorityYear="2008" baseAuthorityName="Jaschhof &amp; Jaschhof" baseAuthorityYear="2008" box="[1156,1252,306,331]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Trichotoca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fraterna">
<emphasis id="B978EAC89532FF827D9FFEE6FB66FEA8" box="[1156,1252,306,331]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="56">fraterna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The clypeus is asetose. The maxillary palpus has a vestigial, asetose basal segment and is thus seemingly 4-segmented (
<figureCitation id="13372A5F9532FF827C76FE8EFF39FE7F" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,255,1934,1958]" captionTargetBox="[193,1378,357,1874]" captionTargetId="figure-118@2.[151,1436,323,1927]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Trichotoca edentula sp. n., male. A: Fourth flagellomere, lateral view (holotype). B: Apical flagellomeres, lateral view (holotype). C: Maxillary palpus, lateral view (paratype from Mt Weld). D: Wing (paratype from Mt Weld). Scale = 0.05 mm for A–C, 1.0 mm for D." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5241999" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5241999/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="56">Fig. 1C</figureCitation>
). The thoracic pleura are asetose. The costa and its cover with setae are not interrupted, i.e. the costal break is missing (
<figureCitation id="13372A5F9532FF827800FE7EFEF3FE27" box="[283,369,426,452]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,255,1934,1958]" captionTargetBox="[193,1378,357,1874]" captionTargetId="figure-118@2.[151,1436,323,1927]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Trichotoca edentula sp. n., male. A: Fourth flagellomere, lateral view (holotype). B: Apical flagellomeres, lateral view (holotype). C: Maxillary palpus, lateral view (paratype from Mt Weld). D: Wing (paratype from Mt Weld). Scale = 0.05 mm for A–C, 1.0 mm for D." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5241999" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5241999/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="56">Fig 1D</figureCitation>
). Male terminalia: The gonocoxites are wider than long, tapered towards the base, and have a shallow, broadly U-shaped emargination ventrally (
<figureCitation id="13372A5F9532FF827A0CFE06FCFAFE0F" box="[791,888,466,492]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,255,1098,1122]" captionTargetBox="[184,1374,188,1048]" captionTargetId="figure-338@4.[151,1436,140,1100]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Trichotoca edentula sp. n., holotype male. A: Terminalia, ventral view. B: Ejaculatory apodeme and tegmen, ventral view. Scale = 0.1 mm for A, 0.05 mm for B." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5242003" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5242003/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="56">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
); the gonocoxal apodemes are apparently not connected by a transverse bridge; the gonostylus is wide basally, tapered in the distal half, and has a rounded, unmodified apex (
<figureCitation id="13372A5F9532FF827875FDF6FE4FFDDF" box="[366,461,546,572]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,255,1098,1122]" captionTargetBox="[184,1374,188,1048]" captionTargetId="figure-338@4.[151,1436,140,1100]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Trichotoca edentula sp. n., holotype male. A: Terminalia, ventral view. B: Ejaculatory apodeme and tegmen, ventral view. Scale = 0.1 mm for A, 0.05 mm for B." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5242003" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5242003/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="56">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
); the ejaculatory apodeme is strongly sclerotized, long, rod-like, very slightly widened apically, and completely mantled by the tegmen (
<figureCitation id="13372A5F9532FF827A06FD9EFCF8FD87" box="[797,890,586,612]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,255,1098,1122]" captionTargetBox="[184,1374,188,1048]" captionTargetId="figure-338@4.[151,1436,140,1100]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Trichotoca edentula sp. n., holotype male. A: Terminalia, ventral view. B: Ejaculatory apodeme and tegmen, ventral view. Scale = 0.1 mm for A, 0.05 mm for B." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5242003" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5242003/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="56">Fig. 2B</figureCitation>
); the tegmen is membranous, large, as long as the gonocoxites, tapered in the distal half, and has innumerable tiny, hook-like spines apicoventrally and -laterally (
<figureCitation id="13372A5F9532FF8279F1FD4EFEC5FD57" box="[234,327,666,692]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,255,1098,1122]" captionTargetBox="[184,1374,188,1048]" captionTargetId="figure-338@4.[151,1436,140,1100]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Trichotoca edentula sp. n., holotype male. A: Terminalia, ventral view. B: Ejaculatory apodeme and tegmen, ventral view. Scale = 0.1 mm for A, 0.05 mm for B." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5242003" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5242003/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="56">Fig. 2B</figureCitation>
); the sternite 10 is very weak and sparsely pubescent. Body length is subequal to wing length, 
<quantity id="4CF49B3F9532FF82798CFD16FEA5FD3F" box="[151,295,706,732]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.85" metricValueMax="4.5" metricValueMin="3.2" pageId="3" pageNumber="56" unit="mm" value="3.85" valueMax="4.5" valueMin="3.2">3.2–4.5 mm</quantity>
. The female is unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C31665519532FF8279DEFD3EFEDCFCB7" pageId="3" pageNumber="56" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BB336DA9532FF8279DEFD3EFEDCFCB7" blockId="3.[151,1436,266,1132]" pageId="3" pageNumber="56">
<emphasis id="B978EAC89532FF8279DEFD3EFEC0FCE7" bold="true" box="[197,322,746,772]" pageId="3" pageNumber="56">Variation.</emphasis>
CuA1 either coalesces at one point with CuA2 and the longitudinal vein (
<figureCitation id="13372A5F9532FF827DBEFD3EFA83FCE7" box="[1189,1281,746,772]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,255,1934,1958]" captionTargetBox="[193,1378,357,1874]" captionTargetId="figure-118@2.[151,1436,323,1927]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Trichotoca edentula sp. n., male. A: Fourth flagellomere, lateral view (holotype). B: Apical flagellomeres, lateral view (holotype). C: Maxillary palpus, lateral view (paratype from Mt Weld). D: Wing (paratype from Mt Weld). Scale = 0.05 mm for A–C, 1.0 mm for D." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5241999" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5241999/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="56">Fig. 1D</figureCitation>
), or joins the longitudinal vein somewhat distal to that juncture. The apex of CuA2 is either strongly (
<figureCitation id="13372A5F9532FF827DC9FCC6FAB2FCCF" box="[1234,1328,786,812]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,255,1934,1958]" captionTargetBox="[193,1378,357,1874]" captionTargetId="figure-118@2.[151,1436,323,1927]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Trichotoca edentula sp. n., male. A: Fourth flagellomere, lateral view (holotype). B: Apical flagellomeres, lateral view (holotype). C: Maxillary palpus, lateral view (paratype from Mt Weld). D: Wing (paratype from Mt Weld). Scale = 0.05 mm for A–C, 1.0 mm for D." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5241999" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5241999/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="56">Fig. 1D</figureCitation>
) or only slightly reflexed.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C31665519532FF8279DEFCB6FCEFFB8F" pageId="3" pageNumber="56" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BB336DA9532FF8279DEFCB6FAEFFC9F" blockId="3.[151,1436,266,1132]" box="[197,1389,866,892]" pageId="3" pageNumber="56">
<emphasis id="B978EAC89532FF8279DEFCB6FED0FC9F" bold="true" box="[197,338,866,892]" pageId="3" pageNumber="56">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name is from the Latin, 
<emphasis id="B978EAC89532FF827BB3FCB6FC9AFC98" box="[680,792,866,891]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="56">edentulus</emphasis>
, toothless, referring to the outline of the gonostyli.
</paragraph>
